    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-28T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="763"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.248/191: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-28T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 28, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 28—9:33
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>640. My 563, November 7, 11 a.m., Russian aid to China. According to reliable
                    sources, the Chinese Government has received some new type of manufactured
                    pursuit planes known as the “E–17”; the number of such planes received was not
                    divulged. The same sources revealed that Russian volunteers decided not to
                    accompany the new craft but that they are being piloted by Chinese pilots.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
